  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dda\u0d9c\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da9\u0dca \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db7\u0dda\u0daf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A fast spreading covid variant in Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Professor Chandima Jeevanda, Head of the Department of Allergy Immunology and Cell Biology at the University of Sri Jayewardenepura, said that the rapid-spreading sub-variant of Covid called Omicron BA 5 has been found for the first time in Sri Lanka.",
        "He also mentioned that due to this rapidly spreading variety, a dire situation may arise in the country in the future.",
        "Stating that this is the sub-type of Covid that is spreading rapidly in the world today, Mr. Jeevandara also stated that due to this, the number of Covid patients in Sri Lanka is likely to increase rapidly.",
        "He further said that this subspecies was found especially in the areas around Colombo and considering this situation it is very important for the people to follow the health rules and act carefully."
      ],
